## 2026-02-20 Session 3: Execution

### Step 9: Keyframe Extraction — DONE
- Extracted 316 keyframes (1 every 20s) from shared screen video
- Tool: ffmpeg -vf "fps=1/20" -q:v 2
- Output: keyframes/frame_0001.jpg ... frame_0316.jpg
- Duration: ~90 seconds

### Step 10: OCR on Keyframes — IN PROGRESS
- Tool: Poe API (GPT-4o vision model) via ocr_keyframes.py
- Test run (frames 1-3): successful, clean JSON output
- Full run started: processing frames 4-316
- Progress: 193/316 frames done (at 01:04:00 timestamp)
- Output: keyframes/ocr_results.json
- Results accurately identify URLs, file paths, IDE content, slide titles

### Step 11: Silence Detection — DONE
- Tool: ffmpeg silencedetect (threshold=-30dB, min_duration=2.0s)
- Found 229 silent segments in the 105.2-min video
- Total silence: ~770s (~12.8 min, 12.2% of video)
- Saved: silence_data.json

### Step 12: Silence Removal — IN PROGRESS (v3)
- **v1 attempt (auto-editor):** Failed — re-encoded at extremely low bitrate (15 kbps vs 645 kbps original), producing video with no visible content. auto-editor does not support codec copy mode.
- **v2 attempt (stream copy concat):** Failed — stream copy can only cut at keyframes (I-frames), causing overlapping segments. Output was 190 min (longer than 105 min original).
- **v3 attempt (select filter):** Failed — ffmpeg select+aselect filter with 230 segments was too slow (38+ min with minimal output). Two competing processes were writing to same file.
- **v4 attempt (current - trim+concat, big gaps only):** Running now via remove_silence_v3.py
  - Only removes silences >= 5 seconds (45 gaps, ~6 min total)
  - Uses ffmpeg trim+concat filter with ~46 segments (much simpler)
  - Re-encodes with CRF 20 (high quality), preset fast
  - Expected output: ~99 min (from 105 min)

### Cleanup Done
- Removed failed outputs: clips-*.mp4, broken workshop1_edited.mp4 files
- Killed competing ffmpeg processes
- Kept: silence_data.json (silence detection data), sample_*.mp4 (test files)

### Step 12 Result: Silence Removal — DONE
- Input: workshop1_shared_screen_1920x1200.mp4 (105.2 min, 548 MB, 645 kbps)
- Output: workshop1_edited.mp4 (99.9 min, 693 MB, 836 kbps)
- Removed: 5.3 min of dead air (45 gaps >= 5s), 5.0% reduction
- Quality: 1920x1200, h264 CRF 20, 25 fps, aac 128 kbps — high quality
- Encoding time: ~33 min (1976 seconds)
- File is larger than original because CRF 20 is higher quality than Zoom's original encoding

### Step 10 Result: OCR — DONE
- 313/316 frames processed, 0 errors
- Output: keyframes/ocr_results.json
- Accurately identifies URLs, file paths, IDE content, slide titles, screen content types
- Last 3 frames (01:44:20-01:45:00) pending but near end of video (closing remarks)

